ed great public affection as Queen Mother for nearly half a century. Even more influentially, it is the name of her daughter  Queen Elizabeth II  (  b. 1926 )."],"variants":[{"name":"Elisabeth","meanings":["The spelling of   Elizabeth   used in the Authorized Version of the New Testament, and in most modern European languages. This was the name of the mother of John the Baptist (Luke 1:60). Etymologically, the name means ‘God is my oath’, and is therefore identical with <i>Elisheba</i>, the name of the wife of Aaron according to the genealogy at Exodus 6:23. The final element seems to have been altered by association with Hebrew <i>shabbāth</i> ‘Sabbath’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Elizabeth Dive was born in 1225, in England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son with Lambert Bussey. She died in 1317, at the age of 92."},"et":{"1225–1317":"1225–1317","1225–1293":"1225–1293","1250–1306":"1250–1306","1225":"1225","1250":"1250","1293":"1293","1306":"1306","1317":"1317","Hougham, Lincolnshire, England":"Hougham, Lincolnshire, England","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1225–1317":"1225–1317","1225–1293":"1225–1293","1250–1306":"1250–1306","1225":"1225","1250":"1250","1293":"1293","1306":"1306","1317":"1317","Hougham, Lincolnshire, England":"Hougham, Lincolnshire, England","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1225–1317":"1225–1317","1225–1293":"1225–1293","1250–1306":"1250–1306","1225":"1225","1250":"1250","1293":"1293","1306":"1306","1317":"1317","Hougham, Lincolnshire, England":"Hougham, Lincolnshire, Angleterre","England":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Elizabeth Dive est née en 1225, à Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec Lambert Bussey. Elle est décédée en 1317, à l’âge de 92 ans."},"de":{"1225–1317":"1225–1317","1225–1293":"1225–1293","1250–1306":"1250–1306","1225":"1225","1250":"1250","1293":"1293","1306":"1306","1317":"1317","Hougham, Lincolnshire, England":"Hougham, Lincolnshire, England","England":"England, Un